{
	"name": "Find Familiar",
	"type": "feat",
	"img": "icons/creatures/birds/corvid-call-sound-blue.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>During a Short Rest</strong> - Magical</p><br><p><strong>Note: To automate these changes to your familiar, add the @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-feats.Item.0zisKrTHAvE09VXL]{Familiar Class} (found in the Feats compendium) to your familiar's character sheet.</strong></p><br><p>You bind a familiar to your service.</p><ul><li><p>Your familiar acts on its own initiative, but follows your commands to the best of its abilities.</p></li><li><p>Your familiar uses the stats of one of any Level 0 &amp;reference[beast]. Its type is either beast or &amp;reference[construct] (if you want a mechanical familiar).</p></li><li><p>Your familiar has an armour class equal to 10 + your proficiency bonus, and 5 hit points. It has a proficiency bonus equal to yours.</p></li><li><p>Your familiar loses any attack it normally possesses, and gains a new attack instead. The new attack has an attack bonus equal to your proficiency bonus + your intelligence, wisdom, or charisma modifier. The attack now deals 1 + your chosen ability modifier damage. Choose whether bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage is most appropriate for your familiar.</p></li><li><p>When your familiar is within 100 feet of you, you can communicate with it telepathically.</p></li><li><p>When you finish a short or long rest, your familiar is revived, teleported to you, and regains all hit points.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
